# Package Documentation Rules

## Module Annotation
- Every module must have @Module annotation on package-info.java
- Include descriptive module name in annotation
- Document module purpose and responsibilities clearly
- Specify dependencies and constraints

## Documentation Content
- Document public API (facade class)  
- List all events published by module
- Specify module dependencies clearly
- Include usage examples where helpful

## Event Documentation
- Document all domain events published
- Specify event payload and timing
- Include event handling examples
- Document event ordering and dependencies

## API Documentation
- Reference facade class as public API entry point
- Document main use cases and workflows
- Include integration patterns with other modules
- Specify module's role in overall architecture

